<value>Educational Labdoo laptops come with the operating system Lubuntu (Linux) which holds a lot of educational software and Open Educational resources (OER) for the children. Labdoo.org recommends to install <a href="http://lubuntu.net/">Lubuntu (Ubuntu and the desktop LXDE)</a>,as Lubuntu does not ask for many resources and runs fast even on older laptops.

Children of any age - Kindergarten, primary, secondary school and high school - benefit from the educational software (Edubuntu) and educational content, offline wikis, barrier-free usage of software, and many more. If possible, install as much as possible on a laptop, as most of the edoovillages do not have access to internet. What you do not install will not be available...

To offer children the best possible installation, there are 3 ways of installation:

<ul>
<li><a href="/content/cloning-laptops-using-prepared-labdoo-images">cloning laptops using prepared images (recommended),</a> </li> 
<li><a href="/content/sanitation-guide-simple-method">installing Lubuntu (Ubuntu + LXDE)</a> and <a href="/content/installation-scripts-overview">more installation scripts,</a></li>    
<li><a href="/content/faq-forum#FAQ05">or leave everything to Labdoo... ;)</a></li>
</ul>

More useful wikis:
<ul>
<li><a href="/content/tips-and-tricks-suggested-solutions">Technical tips and tricks, suggested solutions</a></li>
<li><a href="/content/anpassen-l%C3%A4nderspezifische-anforderungen-tastatur-sprache-hostname-ua">Adapting a laptop to country specific needs (keyboard, language, hostname etc.)</a></li>
<li><a href="/content/list-countries-voltage-and-power-plugs">table countries, power plug and voltage</a></li>
<li><a href="/content/shipping-notes">Shipping notes</a></li>
<li><a href="/content/video-tutorials-0">Video tutorials (English)</a></li>
</ul>
